1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new chapter to title 43 and a new section to chapter
2 54-07 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to the duties of occupational and professional
3 boards and the receipt by the office of the governor of complaints following licensing decisions
4 of occupational and professional boards; and to provide for a report.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. A new chapter to title 43 of the North Dakota Century Code is created and
7 enacted as follows:
8 Definitions.
9 As used in this chapter:
10 1. "Board" means a board, commission, or other agency of state government created or
11 identified in this title to regulate an occupation or profession.
12 2. "Occupation or profession" means activity for which a license is required from a board
13 or similar activity for which a foreign license is required in another state or jurisdiction.
14 Boards - Duties - Licensing complaints - Report .
15 1. A board shall adopt rules to implement this chapter.
16 2. A board shall submit a report to the governor annually and in a manner specified by
17 the governor. Each report must include the following information for the previous
18 calendar year:
19 a. A summary of board activity;
20 b. The number of:
21 (1) Licensees issued;
22 (2) License applicants, including the number of;
23 (a) Total applicants;
24 (b) In - state and ou t - o f - state applicants; and
