1 (c) New and renewing applicants; and
2 (3) Former licensees who failed to renew.
3 3. A board shall provide instructions on the board's website detailing how to submit a
4 complaint following an adverse decision of the board or one of its members in matters
5 relating to licensing.
6 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 54-07 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
7 and enacted as follows:
8 Occupational and professional boards - Licensing complaints.
9 The governor shall develop a procedure through which an individual may submit a
10 complaint to the office of the governor following an adverse decision of a board or one of its
11 members relating to a licensing matter for an occupation or profession. The governor shall
12 establish a procedure to investigate a complaint filed under this section.
